metadata.name: The Living Book #1 #40
metadata.description:
I have been exploring the medium of print for years. Mixing etching, silk-screening, offset, photocopy, risography, drawing and painting to design and craft experimental art books.From the day digital, which had always fascinated me, took over my publishing practice, I always liked to create bridges between these two worlds.

The Living Books is part of this series of hybrid and experimental works where paper and digital resonate.

This issue #1 is made of 64 pages that will be minted by collectors. A book will eventually be printed and the pages will follow the mint order. Each page exists in a cover version (c) and a xerox version (x).

Controls :

• Click to dive into each frame.
• Press C to toggle cover mode.
• Press X to toggle xerox mode.
• Press 1, 2, 3, or 4 to make a capture and download a PNG with a resolution of x1, x2, x3 or x4.

———————

The Living Book #1 by Ferdinand Dervieux, 2022
Made with Unity
License: CC BY-NC-SA 4.0

metadata.name: alchemy(minima) #7
metadata.description:
alchemy(minima) is the companion collection of its older sister (maxima) which tries to explore on the watercolor-like effects caused by the warps.

it is a free mint to thank the holders of alchemy(maxima) and a few friends and supporters who have been with me thru my journey in genart. Thank you from the bottom of my heart.

From the proceeds of the secondary sales of alchemy(minima),

- 40% will directly go to The Processing Foundation,
- 40% will go to the minter,
- 20% will be used to grow my collection.

Enjoy!

metadata.name: Lonely Shapes #15
metadata.description:
Have you ever felt ignored while the world was passing you by? Felt alone in a group while getting the cold shoulder? Wanted to sink into the depths of the earth while being ostracized? 

Well, here’s some relatable shit for you!

Introducing ‘Lonely Shapes’, a visual representation of our relationships with society around us, whether we’re apart of it or feel left out of it. 

Depicted in colourful, lively shapes so it feels just a little less depressing, this is a collaboration between @Sh!g and @pines_willow, which may or may not have been born out of personal experience.

20% of the royalties from this piece will go to the minter

Made with P5. 10% of the proceeds to the Processing Foundation

metadata.name: Притяжение #17
metadata.description:
Inspired by Kazimir Malevich works, “Притяжение” features the connection between shapes, their positions and colours.
Although, as the work tries to develop further into a non-objective world, some real sceneries can still be associated with it.

——————

Rendering takes around 20 seconds at 60 fps, might take longer on older devices.
Press [1…6] to change an image resolution up to 10k.
Press [S] after the image is rendered to save it.

Created using p5.js.
License: CC BY-NC-SA 4.0.

——————

hrunz. — Aug. 2022.

metadata.name: Other ways #148
metadata.description:
Inspired by Paul Klee’s painting « Highways and byways », « Other ways » propose to build your own and unique generative painting.

7 features, including 4 main styles, 8 color palettes, 5 different parameters of the generative process.


Please note that the preview image is more saturated than the real token due to fxhash GPU management.

In Open Live window, press « s » to save the current image.
To get a High Resolution Image : press « r » to change the resolution for high definition, the image will reload and you can then use « s » to save the image (you can change DP in the URL to  a greater value for an even larger resolution in case you want to print it big).
This project is dimensionless, the Preview and OpenLive images are the same.

This artwork was created using p5js and scribble.

TidallyDisruptedStar. Paris. Jan 2022.

twitter : @TidallyD
